
# WordPress Bash install

A bash script allowing to create a base WordPress and automatically make copies of it.

## Features
- Choose to create a new base WordPress to make copies of it, or make copies of an existing WordPress
- Install/update WP CLI
- Install phpMyAdmin if not already installed
- Install/update common PHP packages
- Install base WordPress
-- Download latest version
-- Set up wp-config
-- Create database
-- Suppress default pages & posts
-- Set SEO optimized permaling structure
-- Install a theme (eg. Astra)
-- Install plugins (eg. WP All Import & WooCommerce)
- Make n copies a of base WordPress
-- Export database to copy
-- Copy files
-- Make symbolics links for themes & plugins directories
-- Update wp-config
-- Import database
- Apache configuration

## Usage

 1. Copy sh script on your server
 2.  Execute it: `bash wordpress_bash_install.sh`
 3. Follow instructions
